text: Etadunna Airstrip (IATA:ETD, ICAO:YEDA) is a locally owned, public airstrip in South Australia. == Facilities == There are two runways active at the airstrip: * Runway 1 is the main runway with a length of 1190 m (3904 ft) with an approximate heading of 17/35. * Runway 2 is the secondary runway which has a length of 1160 m (3805 ft) with an approximate heading of 09/27. ==See also== *List of airports in South Australia == References == Category:Airports in Australia Category:Airports in South Australia Category:Far North (South Australia)
title: Etadunna Airstrip
